The President has ordered the declassification of certain materials at the request of several congressional committees. These materials include specific pages from the June 2017 FISA court application in the Carter W. Page matter, FBI reports of interviews with Bruce G. Ohr related to the Russia investigation, and FBI reports of interviews connected to all Carter Page FISA applications. Additionally, the President has instructed the Department of Justice and the FBI to release all text messages pertaining to the Russia investigation involving James Comey, Andrew McCabe, Peter Strzok, Lisa Page, and Bruce Ohr, without any redactions. The purpose of this directive is to promote transparency.